EFG-Hermes to Seek Consent to Sell Egypt Shares Bought on Margin

-- B y   A h m e d   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-03-02T09:46:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/efg-hermes-to-seek-consent-to-sell-egypt-shares-bought-on-margin.html
EFG-Hermes Holding SAE, the biggest
publicly traded investment bank in  Egypt , will not sell stocks
bought on margin by small investors in the North African country
without their permission, it said in an advertisement in  Al
Masry Al Youm  newspaper.  Buying on margin is when investors purchase securities by
borrowing funds from the broker.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  